The paper discusses question answering on tabular data using a semantic parser, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Specifically, the paper focuses on the performance of a specific model (KDG) evaluated over a specific dataset (WikiTableQuestions), which suggests a focus on computational linguistics (CL) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the architecture of the model and its impact on performance, which suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data pruning as a pre-processing step, which suggests a focus on databases (DB) and information retrieval (IR).
